                "Activities": "<section>\n  <h2>Finance Division Operational Activities</h2>\n  <p>The Finance division manages core procurement, payment, and expense processes to ensure budget accountability and operational efficiency. Below are the primary activities and how to engage with them.</p>\n  <ul class=\"efg-detail\">\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Service\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">Procurement and Purchasing</strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">The Order-to-Pay (O2P) process covers supplier onboarding, purchase request creation, PO approval, and invoice processing. For purchases under €25,000, the Requesting Party can submit a PO directly; for purchases above €25,000, a formal Purchase Request must be submitted to Procurement. All purchasing decisions must align with departmental budgets.</span>\n      <a class=\"chip\" itemprop=\"url\" href=\"https://efg.coupahost.com/\">Coupa</a>\n    </li>\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Service\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">Invoice Processing</strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">Invoices require an approved PO (unless a Finance exception is granted). Overspends are managed at the invoice review stage; invoices with >10% overspend or >5,000 EUR require additional approval from the Cost Center Owner or Project Manager.</span>\n      <a class=\"chip\" itemprop=\"url\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Snb9o7EX-i0v9IZA7eNjTNHYbIqrG-HQhGP95PH8QLg/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.snjsq81pt7xt\">SOP: Invoice Processing</a>\n    </li>\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Service\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">Expense Management</strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">Managers are empowered to approve expenses up to 1K EUR for OPEX and 2.5K EUR for COGS. All claims require supporting evidence (e.g., tax invoice) and must be submitted within 30 days.</span>\n      <a class=\"chip\" itemprop=\"url\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1H5l80yZn3CwpBuED24lzavG5HeQ6wB6Rm8u3qSeVMJU/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.16a68wwgpkbk\">SOP: Expense Processing</a>\n    </li>\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Service\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">Prize Money Payments</strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">Prize money for B2C and B2B is managed via the Payment Labs platform. The process involves tournament operations setting up tournaments and funding requests, financial operations processing funding to the FBO account, and the Payment Approval Group submitting payments to winners.</span>\n      <a class=\"chip\" itemprop=\"url\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1v6kkLSOp4MoM7HqX0eWKShPBy87chA4T9CezsJ-EqzQ/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.xmwtp8mikz9l\">SOP: Payment Processing</a>\n    </li>\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Service\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">System Support</strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">For technical errors or access issues within systems like Salesforce, Coupa, or SAP, please contact the IT Helpdesk or the dedicated Slack channel.</span>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n</section>",
                "Calendar": "<section>\n  <h2>Finance Division Meeting and Calendar Structure</h2>\n  <p>The Finance division maintains a structured cadence of meetings to ensure strategic alignment, operational visibility, and effective communication across the department.</p>\n\n  <ul class=\"efg-detail\">\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Event\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">Finance Townhall <span class=\"efg-pill\">Quarterly</span></strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">A department-wide session for company announcements, guest speakers, and individual/team achievements.</span>\n    </li>\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Event\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">Leadership Pulse <span class=\"efg-pill\">Monthly</span></strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">Focused on strategic alignment, escalation handling, and cascading information down to teams. Participants include L1-3 leadership.</span>\n    </li>\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Event\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">Initiative Sync <span class=\"efg-pill\">Monthly</span></strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">An operational meeting for L3 and below to provide visibility on project progress (using the Jira board) and highlight \"wins\".</span>\n    </li>\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Event\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">Functional Tactical</strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">Team-specific meetings led by Matt, Bassem, and Markus to align on day-to-day priorities, unblock tasks, and manage workload. Frequency is determined by the lead of the department.</span>\n    </li>\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Event\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">1:1s: Managers <span class=\"efg-pill\">Weekly</span></strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">Managers are required to maintain weekly 1:1 meetings with their direct reports.</span>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>Sourcing Business Partner Meetings</h3>\n  <p>Specific recurring meetings are held for Sourcing Business Partner alignment:</p>\n  <ul class=\"efg-schedule\">\n    <li><span class=\"n\">Publisher Operations</span><span class=\"t\">Wed · 3:30 PM GMT</span></li>\n    <li><span class=\"n\">EWC/ENC</span><span class=\"t\">Wed · 09:00 PM GMT</span></li>\n    <li><span class=\"n\">O&O</span><span class=\"t\">Wed · 10:00 AM GMT</span></li>\n    <li><span class=\"n\">MENA Operations</span><span class=\"t\">Thu · 10:00 AM GMT</span></li>\n    <li><span class=\"n\">Enterprise Technology</span><span class=\"t\">Tue · 01:30 PM GMT</span></li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <p>For other specific dates and times, please refer to the linked external calendar.</p>\n</section>",
                "Departments": "<section>\n  <h2>Departments</h2>\n  <ul class=\"efg-cards\">\n    <li class=\"efg-card\" itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Organization\"><strong itemprop=\"name\">Accounting</strong><span class=\"desc\" itemprop=\"description\">Period-end closing schedules, chart of accounts, and financial reporting standards</span></li>\n    <li class=\"efg-card\" itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Organization\"><strong itemprop=\"name\">Treasury</strong><span class=\"desc\" itemprop=\"description\">Cash management protocols, banking authorizations, and FX hedging policies.</span></li>\n    <li class=\"efg-card\" itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Organization\"><strong itemprop=\"name\">Tax &amp; Transfer Pricing</strong><span class=\"desc\" itemprop=\"description\">Compliance calendars, intercompany agreements, and jurisdictional tax guides.</span></li>\n    <li class=\"efg-card\" itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Organization\"><strong itemprop=\"name\">Controlling, FP&amp;A</strong><span class=\"desc\" itemprop=\"description\">Budgeting templates, forecasting cycles, and variance analysis frameworks.</span></li>\n    <li class=\"efg-card\" itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Organization\"><strong itemprop=\"name\">Procurement</strong><span class=\"desc\" itemprop=\"description\">Vendor onboarding processes, PO approval workflows, and preferred supplier lists.</span></li>\n  </ul>\n</section>",
                "Description": "<section itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Organization\">\n  <h2 itemprop=\"name\">Finance Division</h2>\n  <p itemprop=\"description\">The EFG Finance Department is the central hub for financial operations and strategy. Its purpose is to streamline internal workflows, ensure consistency across the department, and provide transparency into financial operations. The division serves as the central repository for all financial policies, standard operating procedures (SOPs), and strategic documentation, supporting the professional growth of every team member.</p>\n  <p>The department is organized into five core pillars that manage the various aspects of EFG's financial health and compliance:</p>\n  <ul class=\"efg-pillars\">\n    <li>Accounting</li>\n    <li>Treasury</li>\n    <li>Tax & Transfer Pricing</li>\n    <li>Controlling, FP&A</li>\n    <li>Procurement</li>\n  </ul>\n</section>",
                "Division": "Finance",
                "Extra": "<section itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/CreativeWork\">\n  <h2 itemprop=\"name\">Finance Division Extra Information</h2>\n  <p itemprop=\"description\">Additional resources, governance frameworks, and operational guidelines for the EFG Finance division.</p>\n\n  <h3>Finance Governance & Communication</h3>\n  <p>The Finance division maintains a structured framework for decision-making and information flow. This includes:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Communication Guidelines</li>\n    <li>Roles and Responsibilities</li>\n    <li>Department Townhall Meetings</li>\n    <li>Department Reporting</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p>This framework is designed to provide clarity across the department, ensure transparency, and define appropriate channels for reporting and day-to-day tasks.</p>\n\n  <h3>Masterdata Framework</h3>\n  <p>Finance-owned master data serves as the single source of truth for financial reporting, budgeting, compliance, and strategic decision-making. The framework covers the lifecycle of master data, including:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Creation:</strong> The intake and onboarding of new data points.</li>\n    <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> Ongoing updates to ensure accuracy over time.</li>\n    <li><strong>Management:</strong> The overarching governance and security of the dataset.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>Standardized Templates</h3>\n  <p>To ensure consistency, the Finance division utilizes standardized templates for documentation. These include ready-to-use Word documents for:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Policies</li>\n    <li>Guidelines</li>\n    <li>Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs)</li>\n    <li>Process Descriptions</li>\n    <li>RACM (Risk and Control Matrix) files</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p>Ownership and contact for these templates is held by Charlotta Hjalmarsson.</p>\n\n  <h3>Service Exceptions</h3>\n  <p>Certain services are managed outside of standard procurement workflows due to their nature or regulatory requirements:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Freelancers:</strong> Managed by Division (selection based on professional expertise).</li>\n    <li><strong>Audit Companies:</strong> Managed by ARC (appointed directly).</li>\n    <li><strong>Legal Advisors:</strong> Managed by Legal (per legal policy).</li>\n    <li><strong>Property Taxes & Public Charges:</strong> Managed by Finance (unavoidable costs).</li>\n    <li><strong>Employee Benefits:</strong> Managed by HR (e.g., health insurance).</li>\n    <li><strong>Governmental Service:</strong> Managed by various departments depending on the service (e.g., France Travail, medical employee checks).</li>\n    <li><strong>Banking Services:</strong> Managed by Finance (banking fees).</li>\n    <li><strong>Finance Advisors:</strong> Managed by Finance (under finance spend management).</li>\n    <li><strong>EOR / Payroll Services:</strong> Managed by HR / US ops team (for FTE and freelancers).</li>\n    <li><strong>Advertisement Services:</strong> Managed by Marketing (e.g., TikTok, Instagram, Google, Twitch).</li>\n    <li><strong>Players/Teams:</strong> Managed by Esports (e.g., BootCamp, Team Merchandise).</li>\n  </ul>\n</section>",
